{
  "texts": [
    "ChatGPT's responses tend to be formal in nature due to its programming to avoid informal language.In contrast, humans tend to use more casual and familiar expressions in their answers.8.",
    "If ChatGPT is informed that its answer is incorrect, it may respond by apologizing, acknowledging its potential inaccuracies or confusion, correcting its answer, or maintaining its original response.",
    "The specific response will depend on the context (e.g.",
    "\"I apologize if my response was not accurate.\")",
    "DiscussionIn addition to the previously mentioned points, there are several other potential adverse impacts that large language models (LLMs) like ChatGPT may have on society, which will be discussed below."
